summary: ’Kay, so as excited as I am for Good Omens it’s still gonna be a lil weird for me because the only other thing (that I can...
question: ’Kay, so as excited as I am for Good Omens it’s still gonna be a lil weird for me because the only other thing (that I can remember) that I’ve seen Michael Sheen in as Aro in Twilight. So I’m just going to sit there watching David Tennant fuck around with someone who I’m convinced is a chaotic evil vampire masquerading as an angel for shits and giggles.
answer: Lol!!! I love this image. Personally, I see Michael and think of the recordings I’ve seen of him in Amadeus because my mother loved him in that when I was a kid. So there’s that.

A lovely 10 minute interview with Michael Sheen, David Tennant and Jon Hamm about Good Omens and fun facts from their lives. Also short clip from the Eden! :)

Gems: 

  • Michael: ‘They should be on opposite sides but they come to love each other really.’ David: ‘A Celestial Odd Couple.’

summary: Just learned today that Neil Gaiman wrote “The Doctor’s Wife” episode of Doctor Who and went back and rewatched it just because...
body:
Just learned today that Neil Gaiman wrote “The Doctor’s Wife” episode of Doctor Who and went back and rewatched it just because of that fact, and really how did I not at least guess that was one of his episodes? It was fantastic.

Also, Michael Sheen plays the voice of the evil “House” entity, which I also didn’t realize until today as well, as I was rewatching the episode.
